'That atrocity John can not understand at all - the family are desperately trying to now go back and understand who Jake was because he wasn't the kid they thought he was and tragically all of the warning signs were there of a kid in trouble.'

When Usher suggested there were clear warning signs that his son had issues, John agreed saying: 'yes they were and I'm so sorry I didn't do anything about it.'

'He said he was at times very difficult emotionally - even as a little boy,' Usher said.  

'He also said "I'm sorry I wish i could have done more to understand my son and stop him" and he's finding it very hard to grieve because he's feeling so much guilt,' Usher said.

