To add to Jake's complexities, his mother died from cancer in 2012 and was then looked after by his five older siblings as his parents had divorced years earlier. 

His father described his son as an 'extremely shy' loner who felt alienated from his family and even expressed in one of his blogs that he felt unsafe with his siblings.

He said he felt he should have known about the full extent of his son's bullying.

'I wish I could understand more of what went on,' he told Usher.

But John also feels that his son was brainwashed and believes that he was a 'soft target for' the Islamic recruiters. 

