'I could tell he was brainwashed but they are such a powerful influence.'

His father never wants to hear again the words that his son will be forever known as -  'Jihadi Jake'  but instead hold onto the memory of his beloved son.

'He's trying to preserve a little bit of who the Jake was that he knew and loved - the kid who loved soccer, the kid who used to run around in the backyard and play in the park with his dad

'He said that's the Jake I need to remember - Jihadi Jake I don't even want to hear that name because I don't even know who that person is and that's not my son.' 

